[2] Since the era of Ancient Egypt, the history of makeup began. People of all genders were wearing makeup to protect their eyes from the sun, prevent evil eyes, identify the physical difference between men and women, and gain sexual and baby-making attractiveness. In the Middle age, for instance the 20th Century, makeup was used to identify the class and social statues. At that time, self-identified men didn’t wear makeup. Now, in this generation, many kinds of people, including men, are wearing makeup because SNS developed. However, there are negative effects of wearing makeup. First, making the children’s age of being seen as sexual targets go down. As the speaker said, makeup has been used to attract other people. The Younger generation might become the sexual target if they get used to doing makeup at an early age. Second, accelerating stereotyped views of “normal beauty”. Although the market of cosmetic products has been extended, there is still a stereotyped view of “normal beauty” such as white skin and thin body. It promotes the view by selling their products. Third, it makes people ashamed of themselves. People tried to hide their skins with makeup and this tendency makes people’s confidence lower. To enjoy makeup, we have to use it to express ourselves, not to hide ourselves.
[3] One of the biggest reasons for making them might be producing themselves. Makeup had started in Ancient egypt. In that time, it was done for another purpose, even men did. Then in the Middle Ages, the purpose was changed. People have done makeup to differentiate class and social status. In that time they believed white skin was good, and it had loyalty, and black one symbol of the worker. The situation had changed, and more people became easy to access. Then, another problem arised. For children, they could learn how to apply makeup easier than before, it has a risk that they could have a nubile appearance too early. Also, makeup could affect people, especially young people’s confidence and mental well being. Some people do makeup to hide themselves. However the most important thing is who you are. Makeup is also a good social experience. Then you need to know about many kinds of beauty. Beauty is not just one type. We should try to promote a healthy use of makeup.
